contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionarypar|tele}} '''Tele''' * Tele- is a Greek prefix (pronounced {{IPA-el|ˈtile||Ell-Tile.ogg}} in Modern Greek) meaning "distant". It can be short for [[television]] in [[British English]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[french language|Québécois French]] and [[italian language|Italian]]. * The [[Fender Telecaster]] guitar is nicknamed the "Tele". * [[Lake Tele]], a lake in the Congo known as the home of the Mokele mbembe. * [[Tele, Mozambique]], a town in Mozambique. *[[Tele, Mali]] * The German rock/pop band [[Tele (Band)|Tele]] * A Nickname for the [[Evening Telegraph (Dundee)]]. 'Tele' is pronounced 'tully' in this context. * Turkic ancient tribal confederation (Chinese [[Tiele people|Tiele)]] *[[Telemark skiing]], a style of skiing * Tele- use in medicine; short for telemetry monitoring {{disambig}}
